The Bank of Japan intervened just afterthe Tokyo market opened to support the dollar from fallingbelow 140.00 yen, dealers said.    The central bank bought a moderate amount of dollars toprevent its decline amid bearish sentiment for the U.S.Currency, they said.    The dollar opened at a record Tokyo low of 140.00 yenagainst 140.70/80 in New York and 141.15 at the close hereyesterday. The previous Tokyo low was 140.55 yen set on April15. REUTER&#3;